. On these lines, the Kingdom of Valencia was influenced by arriving from France.    \n*Clear predominance of the architecture of the cultures of the Mediterranean countries respect of the influence of the French Gothic.    \n*The architectural proportions do not change with the arrival of the [[Renaissance architecture|Renaissance]].    \n*Divergence with the classic Gothic style.    \n*Clear influence of [[Flamboyant|Flamboyant Gothic]], which confers uniqueness.\n*Cladding and concealment during the 17th to 19th centuries of the Valencian Gothic by newer styles such as the [[Baroque architecture|Baroque]] or the [[Neoclassical architecture|Neoclassical]], so today much of the Valencian Gothic remains hidden.    \n*Little impact of [[mudejar]] architecture, but in spite of this, there are interesting examples of mudejar architecture in the Valencian Community, that given the occasional use, are of great singularity.\n\n==Architecture==\nThe most important valencian architects of the Valencian Gothic style are: [[Pere Compte]], [[Francesc Baldomar]], [[Pere Balaguer]], [[Andreu Juli\u00e0]], etc. \n\n=== Religious building examples ===\n;Province of Alicante\n* In [[Alicante]], [[Basilica of Santa Maria, Alicante|Basilica of Santa Maria]], [[Concatedral de San Nicol\u00e1s, Alicante|Concatedral de San Nicol\u00e1s]].\n* In [[Castalla]], [[Ermita de la Sangre (Castalla)|Ermita de la Sangre]].\n* In [[J\u00e1vea]], [[Iglesia de San Bartolom\u00e9 (J\u00e1vea)|Iglesia de San Bartolom\u00e9]].\n* In [[Orihuela]], [[Orihuela Cathedral]].\n* In [[Teulada, Spain|Teulada]], [[Iglesia de Santa Catalina (Teulada)|Iglesia de Santa Catalina]].\n* In [[Villena]], [[Iglesia Arciprestal de Santiago (Villena)|Iglesia Arciprestal de Santiago]], [[Iglesia de Santa Mar\u00eda (Villena)|Iglesia de Santa Mar\u00eda]].\n\n;Province of Castell\u00f3n\n* In [[L'Alcora]], [[Iglesia de Nuestra Se\u00f1ora de la Asunci\u00f3n (Alcora)|Iglesia de Nuestra Se\u00f1ora de la Asunci\u00f3n]].\n* 